caption: I've gone to this location 4-5 days a week for the last two years.  Most times everything is quick enough and efficient. It's rare I have any friendly or noteworthy service and still they don't know my name. Today I was incredibly disappointed in the service. I order a pretty unique drink and it was ready but the person calling names was not paying any attention. The man I believe to be a manager was setting the drinks near her and just standing waiting for more drinks. I approached and said "I'm pretty sure that's mine." After asking to repeat my name three times he was very sassy in telling me I should have asked the other person and not him. He then mumbled something I hope I misheard, because it sounded like he said I had an attitude. All that said, I'm done with this location and will be spending much less with Starbucks as a result.
This location is one of my favorites because all the baristas are lovely.  They get bombarded with orders since it's next to the hospital but they are on top of it. A+++

Coffee isn't the #1 reason why people come here. Often, this starbucks has a line, many many people will come to this, THIS starbucks and walk right past not only other starbucks, but most notebly other coffee serving cafes and restaurants as well Knowingly that this one will most likely be pretty busy and will have to wait in line to be served . One morning I told the barista what I'll say in this review. I asked do you know why people were lined up outside before you opened? She replied because they wanted coffee? " No, they didn't come here for coffee. They could have gotten coffee at atleast 5 other places with in a block around here. I'll tell you why they came here, because of the way they feel when they are here. The service they receive, the way they're treated and made to feel while they're at THIS starbucks is why. The customer service here makes them feel so good, happy, appreciated, valued, and important that they would rather wait in line here, than to get coffee anywhere else around near by with no line and no waiting. So no, people don't usually come here for just the coffee. They come here for so much more, more than any cup of coffee could ever give.
